   "body" : "This PR intends to plug some leaks. It specifically implements adherence to the requirement in BDB to close a handle which failed to open (https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E17276_01/html/api_reference/C/dbopen.html):\r\n\r\n> The `DB->open()` method returns a non-zero error value on failure and 0 on success. If `DB->open()` fails, the `DB->close()` method must be called to discard the DB handle.\r\n",
